summary: Executes a prostate cancer health system simulation, processes the resulting data to compute summary statistics, generate calibration tables, and produce representative plots, while allowing users to modify incidence, symptom onset, and progression rates for sensitivity analysis.
business_intent: Enable analysts and decision makers to evaluate and calibrate prostate cancer simulation outputs, assess model performance under default settings, and explore the impact of key epidemiological parameters on health system outcomes for planning and policy development.
